p: The effects of JL-5001 and JL-5002 on the in vitro replication of the wild-type IAV PR8 strain were further assessed, in order to exclude the possibility that JL-501 and JL-5002 were luciferase inhibitors. As Figure 5d shows, both JL-5001 and baloxavir acid significantly inhibited virus replication, while JL-5002 reduced virus replication by only twofold at 5 Î¼M ( p < 0.05, no significance).
